list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: updated WeatherAPI, WeatherEngine, myFile.json to localWeatherForcast.json (more descriptive), WeatherDay.java to WeatherForecast.java (reflects changes) and fill out WeatherForecast object. WeatherAPI updates localWeatherForecast.json and returns a HasMap. WeatherEngine runs WeatherForcast.java initializes and populates an ArrayList = forecastList of type WeatherForcast.java. forecastList holds the 5 day (every 3 hours) forecast that can be accessed by "forecastList[indexOfForcastYouWant].getTemp()" (this will return the temp value from that object in the array). TODO: is to organize the forecastList into days, get average temps for the xml display(display cards? that can expand to show the full forecast for that day)
